The paper deals with formalizing mathematical knowledge using axiomatic and algorithmic theories, which falls under the category of logic (cs.LO). The use of theory graphs and theory morphisms also suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). The comparison of two different formalisms, ${\rm CTT}_{\rm uqe}$ and Agda, suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in terms of implementing and using these formalisms.
